hwQinQ.name: hwQinQ

revisions.description: Modify the description of hwQinQSystemWellKnowMac at 2014-06-10

hwQinQ.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwQinQ.description: The QinQ MIB module is defined to manage the configuration under system or interface view.

hwQinQSystemWellKnowMac.name: hwQinQSystemWellKnowMac
hwQinQSystemWellKnowMac.description: The destination MAC address replacing the original destination macAddress is a well-known multicast address. This well-known multicast address shields BPDUs inner details to allow these BPDUs to be transmitted with a tag through the carrier's network.

hwQinQSystemBridgeRole.name: hwQinQSystemBridgeRole
hwQinQSystemBridgeRole.description: It indicates the Bridge 's location, having two possible values :Customers' Bridge and Providers' Bridge.

hwBpduSystemDropPacketSta.name: hwBpduSystemDropPacketSta
hwBpduSystemDropPacketSta.description: View statistics about the discarded BPDUs.

hwQinQSystemEtherType.name: hwQinQSystemEtherType
hwQinQSystemEtherType.description: The value of tag type is encapsulated in the head of the ethernet frame to distinguish the encapsulated mode between the 802.1Q and QinQ. Default is '8100'h.

hwQinQBpduTunnelEntry.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelEntry
hwQinQBpduTunnelEntry.description: The entry of an interface enabled the QinQ function.

hwQinQEtherEncpsType.name: hwQinQEtherEncpsType
hwQinQEtherEncpsType.description: The value of tag type is encapsulated in the head of the Ethernet frame To distinguish the encapsulated mode between the 802.1Q and QinQ.

hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableOneQBpduTunnel.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableOneQBpduTunnel
hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableOneQBpduTunnel.description: The value indicates whether the 1Q-bpdutunnel is opened, If hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableTwoQBpduTunnel is enabling, then this value should be disable.

hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduTag.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduTag
hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduTag.description: Whether to enable the setting of BPDU Tunnel tag. Default is disabled.

hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableTwoQBpduTunnel.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableTwoQBpduTunnel
hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableTwoQBpduTunnel.description: The value indicates whether the 2Q-bpdutunnel is opened, If hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableOneQBpduTunnel is enabling, then this value should be disable. Default is disabled.

hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTag.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTag
hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTag.description: The tag is inserted into the head of the BPDU ,to support that can be transmitted through the services' network.

hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListLow.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListLow
hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListLow.description: The list describes accessible bode from different vlan (0 to 2047).

hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListHigh.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListHigh
hwQinQBpduTunnelCustomerBpduTagListHigh.description: The list describes accessible bpdu from different vlan (2048 to 4094).

hwQinQRemarkOuterTpid.name: hwQinQRemarkOuterTpid
hwQinQRemarkOuterTpid.description: The value indicates the TPID of outer tag of packets that have two tag and output from the output interface of vlan-switch, If hwQinQEtherEncpsType is enabling, then this value should be 0xffff.

hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduFilter.name: hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduFilter
hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduFilter.description: The value indicates whether the BPDU filter function is enabled. If hwQinQBpduTunnelEnableBpduFilter is enabled, then this value should be enable.

hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable.name: hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable
hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable.description: Used to configure packets'vlan stacking in sub interface, receive one-tag packets and transmit two-tag packets, where the outer-tag inserted is in hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable.

hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingEntry.description: The entry of an interface enabled the QinQ-stacking function.

hwQinQSubIfStackingCEVlanStart.name: hwQinQSubIfStackingCEVlanStart
hwQinQSubIfStackingCEVlanStart.description: When configure ce vlan as a range, hwQinQSubIfStackingCEVlanStart is the start vlan id and hwQinQSubIfStackingCEVlanEnd is the end vlan id.

If a Network Management Application attempts to delete a conceptual row by setting this object to 'destroy' and there are one or more entries in hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable pointing to the row, the agent must also destroy the corresponding entries in hwQinQSubIfVlanStackingTable.

hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgTable.name: hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgTable
hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgTable.description: The control-vlan id and control-vlan's attributes can be configured in sub interface. You must designate control-vlan as QinQ or Dot1q before configuring QinQ-termination function or Dot1q-termination function.

hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgIfIndex.name: hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgIfIndex
hwQinQCtrlVlanCfgIfIndex.description: Index number of the sub interface.

hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag.name: hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag
hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag.description: The service type of the sub interface, by setting hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag to the value (rtprotocolenable), the route-protocol attribute enabled; and by setting hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag to the value (localswitch), the localswitch attribute enabled, which means two tags of packets will be pruned. So if you set hwQinQSubIfType to be dot1q type, you can not specify hwQinQCtrlVlanFlag as localswitch.

hwQinQCtrlVlanRowStatus.name: hwQinQCtrlVlanRowStatus
hwQinQCtrlVlanRowStatus.description: This table can be created and deleted.

hwQinQFlexibleFlag.name: hwQinQFlexibleFlag
